{{Infobox Organization |name = International Association of Master Penmen, Engrossers and Teachers of Handwriting |image = International Association of Master Penmen, Engrossers and Teachers of Handwriting (IAMPETH) logo.png |image_border = |size = 250px |caption = IAMPETH official logo |abbreviation = IAMPETH |motto = |formation = {{start-date|January 1, 1949}} |type = |status = 501(c)3 Non-profit organization |purpose = Educational |headquarters = |location = |region_served = Worldwide |membership = over 1000 members |language = |leader_title = President |leader_name = Debi Zeinert |main_organ = Executive Board |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = [http://www.iampeth.com/ http://www.iampeth.com/] |remarks = }}
The '''International Association of Master Penmen, Engrossers and Teachers of Handwriting''' ('''IAMPETH''') (pronounced "I am Peth") is an international association for practicing and preserving the arts of [[calligraphy]], engrossing and [[penmanship]]. IAMPETH was founded in 1949.
IAMPETH maintains an archive of works of past masters (viewable, in person, only to members during the Annual Conference) in addition to online instruction guides on lettering styles such as [[Copperplate script|Copperplate]], [[Spencerian script]], [[Illuminated manuscript]] production (engrossing) and others.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.iampeth.com/lessons |title=Lessons |publisher=IAMPETH |accessdate=2018-07-07}}</ref> A portion of the organization's collection has been digitally preserved and is available on their Internet Archive profile.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://archive.org/details/@iampeth |title=IAMPETH |publisher=Internet Archive |accessdate=2018-07-07}}</ref> An annual conference is held each year during the months of July or August in a US city. The convention consists of various classes, banquets, and demonstrations.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.iampeth.com/conferences |title=Annual Conference |publisher=IAMPETH |accessdate=2018-07-07}}</ref>
In 2017 IAMPETH introduced a new Certificate Program, replacing the Master Penman Program which was discontinued in 2015. This program allows all members who have been with the organization for three or more years to submit work to be considered for Certificate of Proficiency, Certificate of Excellence, and finally a Master Penman's Certificate. Current application requirements and associated costs are viewable by members only.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.iampeth.com/certificate |title=Certificate |publisher=IAMPETH |accessdate=2018-07-07}}</ref>
IAMPETH is composed of members from various countries. Dues range from $25 to $55 USD. Membership occasionally closes, temporarily, prior to the Annual Conference.
==IAMPETH Goals== *Practice and teach the arts of calligraphy, engrossing and fine penmanship *Restore the teaching of penmanship in schools *Improve the handwriting of young people *Preserve and share with others the rich tradition of American Penmanship.
